{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_27","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-7343-fails-native-image-run-org.apache.lucene-lucene-core-5.0.0-aae05e36\n\nThe most likely failing stage is the remediation/regeneration flow, not Lucene’s native-image runtime itself. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`, the preserved run shows `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0 --stacktrace` and `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0 --stacktrace` passing under Oracle GraalVM `25.1.0-dev+10.1`, but `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar --stacktrace` fails because the JVM cannot load the native-image agent: `Could not find agent library native-image-agent ... libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`. The native test artifacts in `build/tests/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/8328e93858679ba40866d7a94ed3d4ed.out` and `build/tests/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/bbec26bbee34c79b38d9cc309be835d3.out` show a successful native image build and `19`/`19` native tests passing, and `stats/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/5.0.0/stats.json` shows `37`/`37` dynamic-access calls covered.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `build/tests/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/8328e93858679ba40866d7a94ed3d4ed.out`\n- `build/tests/org.apache.lucene:lucene-core:5.0.0/bbec26bbee34c79b38d9cc309be835d3.out`\n- `stats/org.apache.lucene/lucene-core/5.0.0/stats.json`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Verify the CI/preserved GraalVM distribution includes `libnative-image-agent.so` and rerun the metadata-generation/remediation